[1] Philippines (Manila)
Date: Sun 31 Jul 2005
From: Mary Marshall <tropical.forestry@btinternet.com>
Source: China View, 30 Jul 2005 [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-07/30/content_3287410.htm>

Dengue fever kills 73 in Philippines in 1st half [of 2005]
-----------------------------------------------
The mosquito-born dengue epidemic disease has killed 73 people and
infected 5323 others in the 1st 6 months of this year [2005] in the
Philippines, the local newspaper Philippine Daily Inquirer reported
on Saturday [30 Jul 2005].
The Department of Health National Epidemiology Center recorded at
least 5396 cases of dengue, 41 percent higher than during the same
period last year [2004]. Among the infected people, 73 have died
[case fatality rate of 1353 per 100 000 for the 1st half of 2005,
nationwide. - Mod.RY], said the report.
The report quoted Dr. Vito Roque Jr., chief of the center's
surveillance unit, as saying that the number of dengue cases was not
expected to drop until November or December [2005], when dengue is
fully contained.
Outbreaks of dengue have been reported recently in Bulacan, north of
Manila, and some other places, according to the report.
At least 117 children have been infected recently with the disease in
Nueva Ecija province, some 150 km north of Manila, said the report.
--
